Nairobi Deputy Governor Jonathan Mueke has assured more than 120 Wiper aspirants the party primaries will be free and fair. He spoke in Lavington when he met the party&rsquo;s election board and aspirants on Wednesday. &ldquo;I want the board to disclose full information to all aspirants regarding requirements of nomination so that nobody is locked out during the primaries,&rdquo; Mueke said. He also urged the aspirants to mobilise their supporters to register as voters in readiness for the August polls. &ldquo;We will engage in door-to-door campaigns,&rdquo; Mueke said.